text:
@2:30"limiting supply is cost effective"

Rational people would call this a shortage and realize that this results in some people _not getting healthcare_.

@2:49"cared en masse about fixing" Canadians, like the rest of the world, are not in need _en masse_ for crucial healthcare. Most people, for most of their life, don't face crucial healthcare situations. Any modern country can fix broken bones or perform appendectomies. Hell, they did that when I was a kid some 45 years ago.
Those whose life depends on a quick diagnosis of cancer? Not so many.
Excellent example of the appeal to majority fallacy.

Gotta admit, the spin doctor is good. But I ain't buying.
